

=Bio=

"After Engineering studies in France and in the US, he worked on telecommunicatioins engineering projects in France, US and Chile. He served as CTO for OpenPattern developing an OpenHardware FPGA-based router-board. He is currently working for a Linux-based VoIP company managing the development of the XiVO IPBX OpenHardware appliance. He participates in the OHANDA trademark initiative supporting the development of OpenHardware projects."


